# Interfaces to Define and Export

## 1. UniversalBoardViewState

A supporting interface representing a single named state the right panel can be in.

| Field | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| key | string | Named key for this state. e.g. `"journey"`, `"moment"`, `"draft"`, `"idle"` |
| triggerVariable | string | The Board-level variable whose truthy value activates this state. e.g. `"activeJourneyId"` |
| componentName | string | The React component that renders in the right panel for this state. e.g. `"KeeperJourneyPanel"` |
| isShared | boolean | `true` if the component is shared across Boards (KeeperViewPanel, HomeViewPanel, KeeperJourneyPanel). `false` if Board-specific. |
| isDefault | boolean | `true` for the idle/fallback state. Only one view state per Board should have `isDefault: true`. |

## 2. UniversalBoardDataFetch

A supporting interface documenting what a Board fetches on mount.

| Field | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| description | string | Plain-language description. e.g. `"domainId from /api/domains/by-slug/[slug]"` |
| isDuplicated | boolean | `true` if this same fetch exists in one or more other Boards. Documents duplication — does not fix it yet. |

## 3. UniversalBoardSchema

The primary interface. Every Board is an instance of this shape.

| Field | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| boardId | `"ide" \| "agent" \| "domain" \| "designer"` | Canonical key. Maps to boardRegistry.ts keys. |
| displayName | string | Human-readable label used in navigation and registry. |
| access | `{ isPrivate: boolean; isAdminOnly: boolean }` | Access control. Migrated from boardRegistry.ts. Belongs in the schema. |
| layoutEngine | `"panel-group" \| "fixed"` | `"panel-group"` = KeeperBoardPanelGroup (resizable, persisted). `"fixed"` = hardcoded flex. Going forward all Boards use `"panel-group"`. This field documents current divergence honestly. |
| centerPanel | `{ ownsDialogFrame: boolean; componentName: string; }` | `ownsDialogFrame: true` means the Board renders KeeperDialogFrame at root. `false` means a sub-component handles it. |
| rightPanel | `{ viewStates: UniversalBoardViewState[] }` | Named, ordered list of right panel states. Formalizes what is currently scattered inline conditional logic. |
| dataFetches | `UniversalBoardDataFetch[]` | What this Board fetches on mount. Documents duplication. Does not fix it yet. |
| contextDependencies | `Array<"useV0Shell" \| "useFrameContextOptional" \| "useAuth">` | Which context hooks this Board consumes. |
| sharedState | `string[]` | Selection ID variables that live at Board level as useState. Documents current state. Does not change anything. |
| diagnosticNotes | `string[]` | Free-form notes from the diagnostic. Defects, gaps, TODOs. Visible in the schema so they travel with the Board. |

